JavaScript:

```javascript
// Add active class to navbar item on click
const navbarItems = document.querySelectorAll('.navbar-item');
navbarItems.forEach(item => {
  item.addEventListener('click', () => {
    navbarItems.forEach(item => {
      item.classList.remove('is-active');
    });
    item.classList.add('is-active');
  });
});
```

This will add an active class to the clicked navbar item, and remove the active class from all other navbar items.

To remove column A from the data in vertical3, you can use the DROP statement in PROC SQL. Here's the code:

```
proc sql;
    create table vertical3 as
    select Treatment, Effectiveness, Sex
    from vertical2;
quit;
```

This code will create a new table called vertical3, which will contain the same data as vertical2, but without column A.

